definitions.definition: A person, usually a woman , who is trained to assist women in childbirth , but who is not a physician .
examples: A hundred years ago, a midwife would bring the baby into the world - going to a hospital to deliver a baby was either impossible or unheard of.

definitions.definition: Someone who assists in bringing about some result or project.

main_definition: ( obstetrics ) A person, usually a woman , who is trained to assist women in childbirth , but who is not a physician .
secondary_definitions: ( rare , figuratively ) Someone who assists in bringing about some result or project.
